# --- MixTape (added) ---
# TypeScript incremental-build cache (emitted by `vue-tsc --build`) — machine-local, regenerated on every build.
*.tsbuildinfo
# Local-only / host-specific docs — never commit. (The host docs now live in
# docs/host.local/ below; this glob remains for any stray *.local.md.)
*.local.md
# Claude Code local/personal settings.
.claude/settings.local.json

# Home-infrastructure docs — never tracked (see CLAUDE.md -> Docs).
#
# This repo is public. docs/host.local/ holds everything specific to the one
# live server: hostname, LAN topology, MACs, the DynDNS host, the real domain,
# secret LOCATIONS. The generic, reproducible version of the same material is
# docs/self-hosting/, which IS tracked and uses placeholders throughout.
#
# The trailing slash ignores the whole directory. Note the *.local.md rule above
# would NOT cover files inside it (infrastructure.md does not match that glob),
# so this entry is doing real work — do not remove it.
#
# The directory is named generically on purpose: an ignore rule has to name its
# target literally, so a host-named directory would leak the host name into this
# tracked file — the exact thing the rule exists to prevent.
docs/host.local/
